  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Talent Acquisition Specialist (HR Operations)",
  "description": "<p>As part of country expansion, we are looking for a dynamic and versatile <strong>Talent Acquisition Specialist </strong>to be part of the People team. You will be responsible for <strong>anchoring CHAGEE’s expansion and serving as a key partner to the business.</strong> You will also be an integral part supporting of the Group’s strategic expansion and initiatives</p><p>If you are looking to develop your career with <strong>one of the leading global tea beverage brand</strong>; send in your application now!</p><h3>Key Responsibilities</h3><p><strong>Recruitment & Talent Acquisition</strong></p><p><ul><li>Source candidates through job portals</li><li>Manage the end-to-end recruitment process from requisition to offer</li><li>Build and maintain a strong talent pipeline for current and future hiring needs</li><li>Conduct resume screening and initial interviews</li><li>Support mass hiring, campus hiring, and other recruitment initiatives</li><li>Promote employer branding to attract quality candidates</li></ul></p><p><strong>HR Operations & Administration</strong></p><p><ul><li>Handle HR data entry including work permits, account creation, employee files, and system updates</li><li>Prepare and coordinate onboarding documentation and processes</li><li>Manage offboarding activities, including exit interviews and clearance</li><li>Maintain accurate and up-to-date employee and recruitment records</li></ul></p><p><strong>Store Operations Support</strong></p><p><ul><li>Conduct regular store visits to check in with store partners and understand manpower needs</li><li>Support store scheduling and coordination, especially for part-timers</li><li>Assist in payroll preparation, attendance tracking, and manpower reporting</li></ul></p><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Proven experience of 1 to 2 years as a talent acquisition or HR generalist, in a fast-paced environment</li><li>Diploma in human resources or equivalent</li><li>Enterprising mindset and approach</li><li>Good communication and interpersonal skills</li><li>Knowledge of industry, recruitment trends and developments</li><li>Team player, with a keen eye on details</li></ul>",
